                Euro 2017 highlights: England 6-0 ScotlandEngland and Scotland have been drawn in the same group at the 2019 Women's World Cup in France next summer.Japan, World Cup winners in 2011 and runners-up four years later, and Argentina are the other sides in Group D.Scotland, who are making their first appearance at the World Cup, will meet England in Nice on 9 June in what is the group opener for both countries.
    
        
The finals are staged from 7 June to 7 July.England and Scotland met at Euro 2017, with the Lionesses winning 6-0.Reaction to the 2019 Women's World Cup drawEngland and Scotland Group D fixturesJune 9: England v Scotland (Nice)June 14: England v Argentina (Le Havre); Japan v Scotland (Rennes)19 June: Scotland v Argentina (Paris); Japan v England (Nice)More to follow.
 
